org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable, org.eclipse.core.runtime.IExecutableExtension, org.eclipse.ui.IPersistable, org.eclipse.ui.IViewPart, org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchPart, org.eclipse.ui.IWorkbenchPart2, org.eclipse.ui.part.IWorkbenchPartOrientation
public class LoadProject
extends ProjectData

This class is used to populate all the projects present in the file system

It also populate the compositeevent present under every projects and nested composisteevents

It also populate the simpleevent present under every composisteevent, and groupmetrics present under the simpleevent and the atomicmetrics present under both the simpleevent and the groupmetrics.

loadNewProject

public void loadNewProject(java.lang.String filePath,
                           java.lang.String projectName)
This method is used to load all the projects from the file system when user say LoadProject from the right click menu. It will load the new projects if the project is already load then this will not load a duplicate project in the tree

Parameters:
filePath - This of type string which contains the path of the project in the file system
projectName - This of type string which contains the name of the project to be loaded

deleteProjects

public void deleteProjects(java.lang.String adapterPath,
                           java.lang.String projectName)
This method is used to delete the project information from the tree It will delete all the child nodes under this particulate project and also delete the project from the file system

Parameters:
adapterPath - This string which contains the adapterpath under which project is present
projectName - This string contains the name of the project which is going to be deleted

deleteFolder

public boolean deleteFolder(java.io.File file)
This methdod is used to delete the folder. This will recursively delete the subfolders and its files in the file system

Parameters:
file - This is of type File object which contains the folder to be deleted
Returns:
This returns true if all the sub-folders and files and the root folder deleted successfully.
